Hey guys, my friend in optimize wanted me to forward along this message incase anyone is  interested. 

optiMize offers workshops, mentorship, and up to $20,000 funding for students from all disciplines to create self-directed projects aimed at making the world more just and sustainable. Our project submission deadline for the Social Innovation Challenge is October 10 (tomorrow). The application take 10 mins and you don’t even need a project just an idea and all applications will be accepted into the challenge. Even if you don’t have an idea or project many of our teams want to make apps or websites but do not have the technical background so if you are interested in possibly working with one of these teams still apply and come to our first workshop and we will find you a team to work with! The Michigan Marching Band would like to invite all interested students to participate in the upcoming football game halftime show on Oct. 26.  This show is a celebration of the Apollo 11 moon landing and the longstanding relationship between NASA and the University of Michigan.  250 students will be selected to participate by lottery and those with a demonstrate academic or other interest in space related fields will be prioritized.  T-Shirts will be provided to all participants.

To sign up, please complete the sign up form here: <https://forms.gle/Nn7g6oQw7mXErp2K9>

A few items to note:
1.  To participate, you MUST participate in BOTH rehearsals - Friday, October 25 at 7PM and Saturday October 26 4 hrs before game time
2.  Game tickets are not provided nor required to participate (if you have purchased a ticket, you can watch the game from and return to your seat).
3.  If you don’t have a game ticket, you’ll meet us in the second quarter and leave after halftime (more details to follow).
4.  Responses are due by October 11 at 5PM
